oltBaseManageEntry.name: oltBaseManageEntry
oltBaseManageEntry.description: Each entry in this table contain the info for one OLT ( that is also called one PON port)

oltEnable.name: oltEnable
oltEnable.description: This object is used to enable or disable the OLT. When enabled, the olt will pass user traffic; When disabled,the olt will turning off the EPON port and blocking all traffic in both directions

maxPermitLLIDNumber.name: maxPermitLLIDNumber
maxPermitLLIDNumber.description: LLID number that the olt allow to register, this value can only be changed when the olt is disabled.

registeredLLIDNumber.name: registeredLLIDNumber
registeredLLIDNumber.description: LLID number that registered now on this OLT

accessedOnuNumber.name: accessedOnuNumber
accessedOnuNumber.description: The accessed physical ONU number, 'physical' is opposite to 'dummy', a 'Logical Link' is also called a dummy ONU to the OLT

linkIdExhaust.name: linkIdExhaust
linkIdExhaust.description: Indicate if there is available linkId which can be allocated to new registered Logical Link

linkIdOverWrite.name: linkIdOverWrite
linkIdOverWrite.description: Description. This object is used to config linkId overwrite operation. LinkId is system resource managed by PON card firmware and used to identify each Logical Link. When a new Link register, a LinkId will be assigned. When the registered Link off-line or de-register,the assigned LinkId will still be reserved. Such a policy will lead a result that is the allowed linkId resource exhaust. When this occurred, the device manager can have two choices, delete the off-line linkId entry manually or permit the device firmware itself to overwrite the oldest assigned linkId by seting the value of this object to 'yes'. Generally, the choice will be made based on if the user care the off-line Links' configurations and status. If don't care, set this value to 'yes' will be a better choice.

oltOperate.name: oltOperate
oltOperate.description: This object define a collection of operate actions which can be apply on olt device

oltChipInfoTable.name: oltChipInfoTable
oltChipInfoTable.description: Description. reserved, may or may not support

oltChipInfoEntry.description: Each entry in this table contain an olt info

oltOamRateEntry.name: oltOamRateEntry
oltOamRateEntry.description: Each entry in this table contain configurations for each OLT

minOamRate.name: minOamRate
minOamRate.description: Description. Reserved, EMS may not be support

maxOamRate.name: maxOamRate
maxOamRate.description: Description. Reserved, EMS may not be support

oamRspTimeout.name: oamRspTimeout
oamRspTimeout.description: Description. Reserved, EMS may not be support

discoveryParaTable.name: discoveryParaTable
discoveryParaTable.description: Description. Reserved. ONU discovery process parameters. These parameters are associated with the transmit distance

discoveryParaEntry.name: discoveryParaEntry
discoveryParaEntry.description: Each entry in this table contain configurations for each OLT

oltAdvancedConfigTable.name: oltAdvancedConfigTable
oltAdvancedConfigTable.description: This table contain the information which is not normally used but may be usefull in some special circumstance

oltAdvancedConfigEntry.name: oltAdvancedConfigEntry
oltAdvancedConfigEntry.description: Each entry in this table contain the information for one OLT

oltAddiVlanEthType.name: oltAddiVlanEthType
oltAddiVlanEthType.description: Additional Ethernet type to identify vlan frames. 0 1 2 3 --------------------------------------------- vlan EthType| tag upstream | tag downstream | --------------------------------------------- 2byte 1byte 1byte vlan EthType: default 0x8100 tag upstream: 1->use this type to tag upstream, 0->untag tag downstream: 1->use this type to tag downstream, 0->untag

onuUltraLongDistanceTrans.name: onuUltraLongDistanceTrans
onuUltraLongDistanceTrans.description: Description.Reserved. This object is used for enable the ultra-long distance transmission of PON. Normally, this object should not be changed, the disable allowwed transmit distance is 20KM for PON standard. But,if some user want it transmit more longer than standard for some special case, he can set this value to true. When change this configuration, several parameters should be changed internally. Detail operations will not be descripted here.

dynMacAgeTime.name: dynMacAgeTime
dynMacAgeTime.description: OLT Mac leared entry age limit, the value unit is '1s'. Set this value to 0 will disable mac age feature

downStreamResetAgeTimer.name: downStreamResetAgeTimer
downStreamResetAgeTimer.description: Generally, only when olt receive learned mac from upstream (from PON port) will reset the age timer. This object give us an option to let olt reset age timer when received learned mac from downstream (from OLT's SNI port).

macOverWrite.name: macOverWrite
macOverWrite.description: when enable, the new coming MAC will overwrite the oldest learned MAC when the per-link learning buf is full; when disable, the frame with new mac will be dropped when the learning buf is full.

discardUnknownMac.name: discardUnknownMac
discardUnknownMac.description: Discard unknown MAC, set to enable will cause the OLT to drop downstream frames with unknown (not learned) DAs

forwardTagOnSimpleBridge.name: forwardTagOnSimpleBridge
forwardTagOnSimpleBridge.description: Set the object to 'allow' will permit the OLT to forward tagged frames on simple bridge links. Set to 'disallow' will not permit the OLT to forward tagged frames on simple bridges.

linkLevelSizeTable.name: linkLevelSizeTable
linkLevelSizeTable.description: This table contains the configurations that the logical links which can register on each priority level

level0Links.name: level0Links
level0Links.description: Priority level 0 link numbers that the olt will allow to register. Priority level 0 is 'min bw=max bw and the delay is sensitive' this object can only be changed when the olt is diable

level1Links.name: level1Links
level1Links.description: Priority level 1 link numbers that the olt will allow to register. Priority level 1 is 'min bw!=0' this object can only be changed when the olt is diable

level2Links.name: level2Links
level2Links.description: Priority level 2 link numbers that the olt will allow to register. Priority level 2 is 'min bw=0' this object can only be changed when the olt is diable

nonDbaLinks.name: nonDbaLinks
nonDbaLinks.description: TDM level link numbers that the olt will allow to register. this object can only be changed when the olt is diable

dbaDropDownWeightTable.name: dbaDropDownWeightTable
dbaDropDownWeightTable.description: DBA drop down weight configuration table

dbaDropDownWeightEntry.name: dbaDropDownWeightEntry
dbaDropDownWeightEntry.description: DBA drop down weight configuration entry

directionId.name: directionId
directionId.description: Administrativly assigned identification for the purpose to distinguish different data direction

oltPortId.description: Administrativly assigned port ID, used as entry index

priCopyMapTable.name: priCopyMapTable
priCopyMapTable.description: Priority copy value map configuration table

accessUserIdentiferConfigEntry.name: accessUserIdentiferConfigEntry
accessUserIdentiferConfigEntry.description: Description. The PPPOE+ feature act on each OLT (PON port)

pppoePlusEnable.name: pppoePlusEnable
pppoePlusEnable.description: Description. Enable/Disable pppoe+ feature, when enabled PON card firmware will sniff each pppoe require frames sent from user divice and then add cared info (normal info will be onu ID,onu port, vlan ID) to the protocol specified frame field. This feature is usefull when exact user identify is needed. Disable OLT is essential before set this feature.

linkId.name: linkId
linkId.description: this object is defined to identify 'Logical Links' registered on OLT, it is a numbered value begin from 1 to max permit Link numbers. it is used within a OLT range. this object is different from the followwed 'llidAssigned' object,the latter is the LLID value allocated by OLT itself. the 'linkId' is allocated by PON card software.

associatedOnuId.name: associatedOnuId
associatedOnuId.description: Associated ONU ID. the ONU ID that this Logical Link register from

keyChangeTimer.name: keyChangeTimer
keyChangeTimer.description: encryption used key change timer, set to non-zero value will enable down stream encryption, set to zero will disable this feature. the value unit is 'second'.

crossConnectLinkId.name: crossConnectLinkId
crossConnectLinkId.description: the link ID of the link which Cross Connect with this link if it is in Cross Connect Bridge Mode.

linkOamRateTable.name: linkOamRateTable
linkOamRateTable.description: Description. Reserved, generally, the Link OAM rate is used for debugging

llidVlanTag.name: llidVlanTag
llidVlanTag.description: Vlan and translated vlan tags. Data formats: ------------------------------ vlan tag | translated vlan id | ------------------------------ 2B 2B translated vlan tag must be set to 0 if the link is not in vlan translate mode

llidVlanRowStatus.name: llidVlanRowStatus
llidVlanRowStatus.description: Create or delete a vlan tag for a given LinkId

linkIDsInVlan.name: linkIDsInVlan
linkIDsInVlan.description: This object is a linkId container, which contain all the linkIds value which belong to this vlan. Data formats: ------------------------------------------------ link number|linkId0|linkId1|.....|linkIdn|...... ------------------------------------------------ 2B 1B 1B 1B
